e is done.\n\nThe state machine must count for exactly (delay[3:0] + 1) * 1000 clock\ncycles. e.g., delay=0 means count 1000 cycles, and delay=5 means count\n6000 cycles. Also output the current remaining time. This should be equal\nto delay for 1000 cycles, then delay-1 for 1000 cycles, and so on until\nit is 0 for 1000 cycles.\n\nWhen the circuit isn\'t counting, the count[3:0] output is don\'t-care\n(whatever value is convenient for you to implement). At that point, the\ncircuit must assert done to notify the user the timer has timed out, and\nwaits until input ack is 1 before being reset to look for the next\noccurrence of the start sequence (1101).\n\nThe circuit should reset into a state where it begins searching for the\ninput sequence 1101. The reset signal is active high synchronous. Assume\nall sequential logic is triggered on the positive edge of the clock.\n\n\n</input_spec>\n<failed_sim_log>\n{\n    "stdout": "",\n    "stderr": "./output_t22c_qwen3coder30b_shard4_0/VERILOG_EVAL_V2_Prob156_review2015_fancytimer/tb.sv:114: syntax error\\n./output_t22c_qwen3coder30b_shard4_0/VERILOG_EVAL_V2_Prob156_review2015_fancytimer/tb.sv:114: error: Invalid module item.\\n./output_t22c_qwen3coder30b_shard4_0/VERILOG_EVAL_V2_Prob156_review2015_fancytimer/tb.sv:115: syntax error\\n./output_t22c_qwen3coder30b_shard4_0/VERILOG_EVAL_V2_Prob156_review2015_fancytimer/tb.sv:115: error: Invalid module item.\\n./output_t22c_qwen3coder30b_shard4_0/VERILOG_EVAL_V2_Prob156_review2015_fancytimer/tb.sv:116: syntax error\\n./output_t22c_qwen3coder30b_shard4_0/VERILOG_EVAL_V2_Prob156_review2015_fancytimer/tb.sv:116: error: Invalid module item.\\n./output_t22c_qwen3coder30b_shard4_0/VERILOG_EVAL_V2_Prob156_review2015_fancytimer/tb.sv:118: syntax error\\n./output_t22c_qwen3coder30b_shard4_0/VERILOG_EVAL_V2_Prob156_review2015_fancytimer/tb.sv:118: error: Invalid module item.\\n./output_t22c_qwen3coder30b_shard4_0/VERILOG_EVAL_V2_Prob156_review2015_fancytimer/tb.sv:119: syntax error\\n./o